HEADWORD: Calliopsis
<hw>Cal`li*op"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. pref. <grk>kalli-</grk> (fr. <grk>kalo`s</grk> beautiful) +
<grk>'o`psis</grk> appearance.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A popular
name given to a few species of the genus <gen>Coreopsis</gen>,
especially to <spn>Coreopsis tinctoria</spn> of Arkansas.</def>⟦br⟧
